  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-05-02 23:32 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] HL is funded but now correctly notional-blocked\n\n**Task:** Audit the first funded-wallet HL live cycles after the signer repair and ensure small-account order sizing cannot fire dust / rejected notional orders.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P3**.\n- Live state before this pass showed the repaired HL engine running funded: status `live`, cycle `147`, wallet `0x4Bf93279060fB5f71D40Ee7165D9f17535b0a2ba`, balance `$37.391639`, `wallet_blocked=false`, `misaligned=false`, positions `0`, signals `0`.\n- Log audit after the 22:56 funded-wallet restart showed clean cycles: repeated `wallet alignment ok`, balance stayed `$37.39`, no positions opened, and no signals since repair.\n- I inspected execution sizing in `/home/ubuntu/clawd/hyperliquid-trader/hl_live_trader.py`: `balance * max_position_pct * leverage` = `$37.391639 * 0.10 * 3 = $11.217492` planned notional.\n- `$11.22` is within the 10% capital risk rule, but too small to rely on as a robust HL order notional.\n- I patched the live trader to add a conservative notional guard:\n  - `self.min_order_notional_usd = 20.0`\n  - `write_live_state()` now publishes `planned_order_notional`, `min_order_notional_usd`, and `order_notional_blocked`\n  - `run_cycle()` skips any signal whose planned notional is below the minimum and logs the skip instead of attempting an order\n- Validation passed:\n  - `python3 -m py_compile /home/ubuntu/clawd/hyperliquid-trader/hl_live_trader.py` \u2705\n  - dry inspection resolved funded wallet and planned notional `$11.2175` \u2705\n  - restarted only `hl-bot` \u2705\n  - post-restart telemetry shows status `live`, balance `37.391639`, planned order notional `11.217492`, min order notional `20.0`, `order_notional_blocked=true`, `wallet_blocked=false` \u2705\n- I wrote the artifact to `/home/ubuntu/clawd/research/p3-hl-funded-cycle-notional-guard-2026-05-02-2332.md`.\n\n**My thinking:** HL is no longer wallet-blocked; it is now intentionally notional-blocked. That is the right state. The engine can monitor and publish clean telemetry, but it will not attempt marginal dust orders just because the wallet clears the basic `$10` balance floor.\n\n**Decision:** Keep HL live trader running on the funded wallet. Keep max trade exposure at 10% capital / 3x. Add a `$20` minimum planned notional gate for new HL entries. Do not open new HL positions until balance or sizing produces planned notional >= `$20`.\n\n**Next:** Decide whether HL should remain monitor-only until capital is moved in, or whether a separate micro-account strategy with explicit smaller-market minimums is worth building. For now, avoid forcing trades from a `$37.39` wallet.\n\n## 2026-05-02 23:16 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] Risk-easing shadow tape supports the current price band\n\n**Task:** Use the fresh P4 state (`mixed_transition`, PM risk `low`, fast `RANGE`, posture `risk_easing`, breakout `",
